{
  "title": "ISic000814. Architrave recording two duumvirs",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ἐπὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"δυῶν\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">δυῶν</span>  <span data-text=\"ἀνδρῶν\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ἀνδρῶν</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span>· <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span><span data-text=\"Λ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">Λ</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΠΙ</span><span data-text=\"δυῶν\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΥΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἀνδρῶν\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΝΔΡΩΝ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-text=\"Λ\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">Λ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic000814_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-11-10\" src=\"ISic000814_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-11-10\" src=\"ISic000814-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy1_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy1_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy1.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy1-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy2_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy2.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy2-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy3_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy3_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000814_copy3.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic000814_copy3-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>In the dummvirate of L[---]</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The reference to <span class=\"italic\">duumviri</span> implies Roman administration of the city, which requires a date after 44 BC. Wilson and Manganaro both take this to imply that the text must belong in the narrow window of the civil war period, 44-36 BC, under Sextus Pompeius, but this is largely predicated on the assumption that the use of Greek would be impossible subsequently in a city of municipal status, whereas the widespread existence of (Latin) municipia on the island from some time in the Augustan period is clear, and the occasional use/persistence of Greek into the Augustan period is also attested, so restriction to such a narrow window of time seems unnecessary. The example of the Greek inscription on the gymnasium benches (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001418\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001418</a>), which appears to be clearly Augustan in date, and the further indication that this stone comes from the portico of the gymnasium </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1966.0168bis <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283</a>  </li><li> Griffo 1963 178-179 no.8 tav.57 fig.9-10 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001936\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001936</a>  </li><li> De Waele 1971 37-38 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002040\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002040</a>  </li><li> Moretti 1976 184 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736</a>  </li><li> Griffo 1985 53 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001935\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001935</a>  </li><li> Griffo 1987 190-192 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001934\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001934</a>  </li><li> Wilson 1990 360 n.89 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a>  </li><li> Fiorentini 1996 13 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001984\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001984</a>  </li><li> Fiorentini 2009 101 n.5 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001983\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001983</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Regular letters, deep cut without serifs. Epsilon has equal length bars; P has equal vertical strokes and no overhang on the horizontal; omega is closed (some variation on the position of the horizontal) and slightly smaller than the other letters; alpha has straight bar. There is a circular interpunct and space before the final letter.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Δ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.1.1</a> </p> Line 1  85-100  Interlineation line 1 to 2  n/a  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
